The paper deals with the preservation of first-order formulas under homomorphisms on classes of structures, which is a topic in mathematical logic and model theory. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses classes of structures with bounded expansion and locally excluding minors, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper uses techniques from graph theory and combinatorics, which are also relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper's results have potential applications in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for reasoning about structured data.
